%description:
TCP Fast Open (RFC 7413), end to end, both roles, two connections through the
same client/server Tcp modules:
 - Connection 1 (port 1000): client has no cached cookie yet, so the SYN is
   sent immediately with an empty ("request a cookie") Fast Open option; the
   server generates and echoes a fresh cookie in the SYN-ACK; the client
   learns it.
 - Connection 2 (port 1001), started before connection 1 closes: the client
   now has a cached cookie, so it defers the SYN until the app's first SEND,
   then sends a SYN carrying both the cached cookie and the data. The server
   validates the cookie (strict mode -- not lenient, so this proves real
   validation, not blanket acceptance) and accelerates: the SYN-ACK's ack
   number covers the SYN and the data in one segment, before the 3WHS
   completes.

Falsification: writing this test caught two real bugs before this recorded
trace was correct -- (1) the deferred SYN is sent from TCP_S_SYN_SENT, not
TCP_S_INIT, which writeHeaderOptions()'s option-append guard didn't
recognize, so connection 2's SYN silently carried no options at all; (2)
insertBytesFromSegment() indexes payload by the segment's own SequenceNo,
which for a SYN-bearing segment is the SYN's own sequence number, not the
data's (off by one) -- srv_app received 199 bytes instead of 200 and the
SYN-ACK's ack number was short by 1 until fixed. Both are now fixed in
TcpConnectionEventProc.cc/TcpConnectionUtil.cc/TcpConnectionRcvSegment.cc;
this test's exact byte/ack assertions below would fail again if either
regressed.

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""
*.cli_app.fastOpen=true
*.cli_app.active2=true
*.cli_app.tOpen2=0.5s
*.cli_app.localPort2=1001
*.cli_app.tSend2=0.5s
*.cli_app.sendBytes2=200B

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""
*.srv_app.active2=false
*.srv_app.tOpen2=0.5s
*.srv_app.localPort2=2000

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.cli_tcp.fastopenClientEnabled = true
*.srv_tcp.fastopenServerEnabled = true
*.srv_tcp.fastopenLenientCookieValidation = false

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 1 (port 1000): no cached cookie -- bare SYN requests one, server issues a fresh one, client learns it.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=0)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Connection 2 (port 1001): cached cookie -- deferred SYN carries the cookie AND 200 bytes of data.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.501 A003] A.1001 > B.2000: S 125000:125200(200) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize NOP NOP FastOpen(cookieLen=8)
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Accelerated ACK: ack 125201 = IRS+1+200, covering the SYN and the data in one segment, no MSS/WS/SACK
%# renegotiation options this time around (a plain accelerated SYN-ACK, not a cookie-issuing one).
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.503 B002] A.1001 < B.2000: A S 125500:125500(0) ack 125201 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
TcpTestNet1.srv_app: received 200 bytes in 1 packets
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
